variables.description: Very subtle (often used for ghost hover backgrounds).

effectStyles.name: shadow-xs
effectStyles.description: Contact state. Use for Input Fields (Sunken), active borders, or pressed states where items feel flush with the surface.

effectStyles.name: shadow-sm
effectStyles.description: Touch state. Use for clickable interactive elements like Buttons, list items, or small chips that need a subtle lift.

effectStyles.name: shadow-md
effectStyles.description: Float state. The default elevation for Cards, Panels, and Content Containers. Defines distinct separation from the background

effectStyles.name: shadow-lg
effectStyles.description: Lift state. Use for Hover interactions on cards, sticky navigation headers, Dropdown menus, or Tooltips

effectStyles.name: shadow-xl
effectStyles.description: Focus state. Max elevation. Use exclusively for Modals, Dialogs, Lightboxes, and blocking alerts that float above everything else.
